00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:25.710
First, what are the considerations?

00:07:25.770 --> 00:07:28.980
You want it to have the card
to have a logical structure.

00:07:29.280 --> 00:07:32.350
This is especially important for screen
reader users, for example,

00:07:32.510 --> 00:07:35.950
where all the information needs to be
in the semantic structure.

00:07:37.080 --> 00:07:39.820
You want to have
a specific visual layout.

00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:41.920
Also, I'm a developer.

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:45.490
I get designs from a designer
and so I have some-

00:07:45.560 --> 00:07:48.260
I have a specific visual layout that
I need to achieve.

00:07:50.670 --> 00:07:53.300
Then also I want to ensure
that it is interactive

00:07:53.370 --> 00:07:57.220
because that's the core
requirement for a card.

00:08:01.280 --> 00:08:03.780
Then I have--
Let's tackle the first thing first.

00:08:03.950 --> 00:08:06.750
The having multiple parts in a row.

00:08:06.810 --> 00:08:12.190
Here I'm showing, again, my little grid
with the preview with the cards,

00:08:12.550 --> 00:08:15.260
six cards in the grid.

00:08:15.990 --> 00:08:19.330
Now I'm going to show the bad
example first.

00:08:19.390 --> 00:08:22.100
If you mark this up with just divs,

00:08:23.100 --> 00:08:27.440
here on the left side,
I have an example, HTML markup,

00:08:27.500 --> 00:08:31.740
where it's just divs as the container
and then divs for each of the cards.

00:08:32.310 --> 00:08:35.910
That doesn't give any information
about what this actually is.

00:08:35.980 --> 00:08:37.950
For example, to a screen reader.

00:08:41.220 --> 00:08:43.990
Another example that you can do,
which is a bit better,

00:08:44.050 --> 00:08:48.520
is you, for example,
use a main tag for the container.

00:08:49.020 --> 00:08:53.490
And each of the cards
are in an article tag.

00:08:53.930 --> 00:08:56.400
This is a bit better
because this gives us

00:08:56.400 --> 00:09:01.100
some actual information
about what this is

00:09:01.170 --> 00:09:03.970
to a screen reader.

00:09:04.140 --> 00:09:06.710
The screen reader can give the users

00:09:10.180 --> 00:09:12.380
more information, more features.

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:15.280
For example, with the main tag,
this would show up

00:09:15.350 --> 00:09:18.990
if somebody uses the screen reader
and navigates through the landmarks,

00:09:19.820 --> 00:09:23.420
they could directly go
to the main content with this

00:09:23.990 --> 00:09:27.030
but there's still a problem
with the article.

00:09:27.860 --> 00:09:31.800
Actually, not all screen readers
have this as a landmark.

00:09:32.170 --> 00:09:34.900
For, I think, only JAWS announces

00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:37.670
it as a landmark.

00:09:38.070 --> 00:09:42.780
Still, even though you're using
a semantic HTML5 element,

00:09:43.010 --> 00:09:47.080
you're not really giving much information
to screen reader users.

00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:51.390
Now a better example,

00:09:51.510 --> 00:09:54.910
and this is best practice,
is to have it as a list markup.

00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:59.260
Here, I've shown it
as a basic HTML example

00:09:59.490 --> 00:10:02.930
with an unnumbered list tag,

00:10:03.300 --> 00:10:06.200
and then each of the cards
in a list item.

00:10:06.530 --> 00:10:09.900
What this gives you is--
This gives a really good-

00:10:09.970 --> 00:10:12.670
because it is a card of one of many.

00:10:13.470 --> 00:10:17.750
A list gives that information
to a screen reader user.

00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:19.440
This is the list of,

00:10:19.650 --> 00:10:22.680
and then the screen reader will announce,
six items,

00:10:22.750 --> 00:10:26.320
and there's some navigation features
that also come with that in

00:10:26.390 --> 00:10:27.600
the screen reader.

00:10:28.390 --> 00:10:30.930
Now, I took a look at what

00:10:30.990 --> 00:10:33.730
most WordPress themes use.

00:10:34.960 --> 00:10:39.770
Most, especially the commonly used ones,
the page builders,

00:10:40.840 --> 00:10:43.570
don't use the list markup for cards.

00:10:43.640 --> 00:10:46.970
I've actually seen more often
the article markup

00:10:48.180 --> 00:10:51.450
and here, a shout out
to Amber Hinds of Equalize Digital,

00:10:51.950 --> 00:10:57.060
because she analyzed 10-page builders,
and they're only two use the list markup

00:10:57.220 --> 00:10:58.790
for their blog or posts loop.

00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:03.160
This is definitely something
that a lot of the WordPress

00:11:03.220 --> 00:11:05.930
themes and page builders are lacking.

00:11:07.530 --> 00:11:09.860
That's why, for example,
I work with GeneratePress,

00:11:09.860 --> 00:11:14.280
and they also have an article markup
and so I'm also often building

00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:16.930
my own loops
with my own cards.

00:11:18.530 --> 00:11:21.350
I also want to mention kudos
to Avada and Bricks

00:11:22.110 --> 00:11:26.730
because they were the two-page builders
that use list markup in this test.

00:11:30.520 --> 00:11:33.490
Now we've decided we're going to have
this as a list markup and here

00:11:33.550 --> 00:11:38.330
I have a very basic HTML markup

00:11:38.480 --> 00:11:41.030
for the item itself, for the card itself.

00:11:41.800 --> 00:11:46.430
For this simple card, just as a reminder,
it has a preview and this is the image,

00:11:46.730 --> 00:11:51.940
it has a title, it has a little
descriptive text, and a read more link.

00:11:53.020 --> 00:11:55.220
Sometimes I say button,
which is not correct

00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:58.370
but I mean, a read more link.

00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:03.420
The basic HTML markup
that we're going to work with

00:12:03.570 --> 00:12:06.120
is just as a list item.

00:12:06.650 --> 00:12:08.260
I've given it a class of card,

00:12:08.420 --> 00:12:11.160
thenit has an image.

00:12:11.860 --> 00:12:14.430
Here I've kept the alternative text empty

00:12:14.500 --> 00:12:17.770
and we're going to talk about images,
so don't you worry.

00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:21.740
Then the title I've marked up
as an h2 headline

00:12:21.940 --> 00:12:25.170
and the description just as a paragraph

00:12:25.240 --> 00:12:27.570
and then I have the link

00:12:27.910 --> 00:12:29.460
at the bottom.

00:12:34.050 --> 00:12:37.490
This is generally like

00:12:37.750 --> 00:12:42.660
sign markup
but the problem is with the link.

00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:45.430
Here, for example, only the read

00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:48.330
more link is actually linked

00:12:48.400 --> 00:12:51.470
but that's not usually
what you expect of a card.

00:12:51.530 --> 00:12:56.270
You expect it like when I'm on my phone,
I want to be able to click on the image

00:12:56.340 --> 00:12:58.330
and it directly brings me
to the article.

00:12:58.680 --> 00:13:03.060
I think this is also what
if you're designing a card element

00:13:03.170 --> 00:13:04.810
that's a marketing banner

00:13:04.880 --> 00:13:09.550
that your marketing people will also want
to increase the click area.

00:13:11.490 --> 00:13:17.660
What I see in a lot of WordPress themes
is that they solve

00:13:17.730 --> 00:13:20.430
this by just adding links
to all of the elements.

00:13:21.530 --> 00:13:28.170
For example, this is an example image

00:13:28.240 --> 00:13:31.110
from the GeneratePress solar demo site.

00:13:31.840 --> 00:13:34.540
I'm just showing a lot of GeneratePress,
not because they are bad,

00:13:34.680 --> 00:13:36.840
just because that's the theme
that I usually work with.

00:13:36.840 --> 00:13:39.550
It's actually a really cool theme.

00:13:39.730 --> 00:13:42.550
Here you can see they have
also a basic card

00:13:42.730 --> 00:13:44.290
that leads to a blog article

00:13:45.050 --> 00:13:48.660
and it has also an image,
it has some categories too

00:13:49.720 --> 00:13:53.060
and it has a title
and it has a read more link.

00:13:53.130 --> 00:13:56.060
Very similar to what we're working with
but here they've solved

00:13:56.130 --> 00:13:58.930
this issue of increasing the click area
by adding

00:14:00.300 --> 00:14:02.000
a link tag around

00:14:02.150 --> 00:14:05.540
the image, around the title
and around the read more.

00:14:05.610 --> 00:14:08.310
You have three links
leading to the same destination.

00:14:08.420 --> 00:14:10.000
This is not good.

00:14:12.110 --> 00:14:15.050
What this will lead to,
like here, for example,

00:14:15.120 --> 00:14:19.220
if you're using the Wave accessibility
testing tool, this will throw errors.

00:14:19.590 --> 00:14:22.260
Here, the error,

00:14:22.360 --> 00:14:25.530
I screenshotted the error,
it says redundant link

00:14:25.690 --> 00:14:28.400
and then a lot of icons
that show, okay, here's an error.

00:14:29.760 --> 00:14:32.870
The explanation for it is that adjacent

00:14:33.170 --> 00:14:36.240
links go to the same destination
and that is bad practice

00:14:36.300 --> 00:14:40.140
because it is confusing
if you're using a screen reader and also

00:14:41.210 --> 00:14:42.380
it's just redundant.

00:14:42.410 --> 00:14:44.440
It's adding a lot of noise.

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:51.150
are we back to just keeping the link

00:14:51.220 --> 00:14:53.620
as the, on the read more button?

00:14:53.690 --> 00:14:56.110
No, there's a better solution.

00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:58.630
We want to work with only one link,

00:14:58.630 --> 00:15:00.800
but have the whole card clickable

00:15:02.460 --> 00:15:04.670
and because if we're only having it

00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:08.040
on the read more link, what happens then

00:15:08.370 --> 00:15:12.270
if a screen reader users
navigate the site because

00:15:13.470 --> 00:15:16.040
by listing out all the link

00:15:16.110 --> 00:15:21.050
elements on the page,
this is one way that screen reader users

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:24.920
can navigate a page by saying,
"Okay, give me all of the links,"

00:15:24.990 --> 00:15:27.790
then what happens is
that it just says read

00:15:27.860 --> 00:15:30.860
more, read more, read more
and it's not descriptive.

00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:32.830
This is definitely not a good solution.

00:15:33.080 --> 00:15:34.950
We can't do it like that.

00:15:38.900 --> 00:15:41.600
The best practice would be

00:15:42.200 --> 00:15:46.640
to just ask yourself, "Okay,
what is the most important,

00:15:46.710 --> 00:15:50.110
the most descriptive element
on this card?"

00:15:50.180 --> 00:15:53.650
and I think that is here in this case,
it's the headline.

00:15:54.320 --> 00:15:58.820
We put the title here, I'm showing
the basic HTML markup again.

00:15:58.890 --> 00:16:03.820
We're putting the link tag inside
of the headline.

00:16:04.830 --> 00:16:08.460
Now we don't need the read
more button anymore.

00:16:10.400 --> 00:16:12.570
We're going to discuss this
a little bit later if that's really true

00:16:12.570 --> 00:16:16.870
but for now,
we have now a good markup that gives

00:16:17.140 --> 00:16:19.810
