00:48:24.890 --> 00:48:30.190
features that screen readers provide users
for specifically for lists.

00:48:30.630 --> 00:48:32.790
This is where you can give screen

00:48:32.790 --> 00:48:35.330
readers the most benefit, I think.

00:48:35.730 --> 00:48:38.200
Otherwise, they just wouldn't have
that input.

00:48:39.730 --> 00:48:40.840
<v Sherose> Thank you, Tina.

00:48:41.440 --> 00:48:45.270
We have time for one more question
and you did cover this,

00:48:45.370 --> 00:48:47.880
but if you could cover it one more time
just briefly?

00:48:48.080 --> 00:48:51.010
What is the benefit of accessibility

00:48:51.110 --> 00:48:55.380
benefit of making the entire card
clickable versus

00:48:56.020 --> 00:48:58.520
having just one clickable element
within it,

00:48:58.820 --> 00:49:00.800
for example, the headline?

00:49:05.290 --> 00:49:07.800
<v Tina> This is a question you can make

00:49:08.500 --> 00:49:12.270
just the headline clickable,
and this would be compliant

00:49:12.370 --> 00:49:16.570
and I wouldn't flag it as like,
"Oh, this is an accessibility mistake,"

00:49:16.670 --> 00:49:17.670
or something like that.

00:49:17.770 --> 00:49:21.080
No, this is more about usability.

00:49:21.280 --> 00:49:24.950
I don't know about other people,
but when I see a blog list,

00:49:25.910 --> 00:49:28.720
blog articles, and their images, I try,

00:49:28.950 --> 00:49:34.260
especially on mobile, I click on the image
and I expect it to lead to the article,

00:49:34.360 --> 00:49:36.770
and so I think it's something
that we're used to

00:49:36.910 --> 00:49:38.390
because a lot of cards do it.

00:49:38.560 --> 00:49:41.060
Also in accessibility, you have to

00:49:42.840 --> 00:49:44.300
take into consideration

00:49:44.300 --> 00:49:45.800
what people are used to.

00:49:46.550 --> 00:49:48.340
Then I also think that

00:49:48.480 --> 00:49:52.270
if you can have a bigger click area,
it is good, for example,

00:49:52.370 --> 00:49:54.080
for people with motor issues.

00:49:56.380 --> 00:50:00.180
Sometimes it's also a requirement
that the designer says, like, "Hey,

00:50:00.250 --> 00:50:02.110
I want this whole thing clickable."

00:50:02.240 --> 00:50:04.120
It's a usability thing.

00:50:04.220 --> 00:50:05.860
It's not a mistake.

00:50:07.020 --> 00:50:10.130
<v Sherose> What I hear from you
then is either option

00:50:10.200 --> 00:50:12.330
would meet WCAG criteria,

00:50:12.430 --> 00:50:17.100
if that's what you're using, either option
but there is

00:50:17.300 --> 00:50:20.430
the larger touch area
and a more common experience

00:50:20.540 --> 00:50:23.530
in making the card itself
clickable entirely.

00:50:23.660 --> 00:50:26.060
